OL,3,CMother of woman murdered by boyfriend
OL,4,Cin his home calls for tougher sentences
OL,6,FThe trial heard that after the
OL,7,Fkilling, Mannion told interviewing
OL,8,Fofficers that he and Miss O'Brien had
OL,9,Fargued after she asked if he was
OL,10,Fseeing other women, when he failed to
OL,11,Frespond to a number of texts.
OL,13,FIn the weeks before he stabbed Miss
OL,14,FO'Brien, Mannion had revealed that
OL,15,Fanother woman he had been seeing had
OL,16,Ftold him she was pregnant.
OL,18,FBut a jury found him guilty of murder,
OL,19,Fwounding with intent, and coercive or
OL,20,Fcontrolling behaviour.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
